diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index 32d08e0..fe3b6e3 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -111,3 +111,25 @@ python scripts/plot_results.py results/summary.csv --out-dir results/plots
 - Add block-local grouping experiments with `blockSize={32,64,128,256,512}`.
 - Replace the dependency-free QMC engine with OpenQMC as an optional backend.
 - Add a 2D polygon/FCPW backend after the toy results stabilize.
+
+## Optional OpenQMC Sobol backend
+
+This prototype can be built with OpenQMC to compare all RQMC schedules using the same Owen-scrambled Sobol backend.
+
+```powershell
+git submodule add https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/openqmc.git external/openqmc
+git submodule update --init --recursive
+cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DWOST_TOY_USE_OPENQMC=ON
+cmake --build build --config Release --parallel
+
+.\scripts\run_openqmc_sobol.ps1
+```
+
+The important distinction is not the Sobol implementation itself, but the scheduling:
+
+- `pathwise-rqmc`: one high-dimensional Sobol point per walk; the step id maps to Sobol dimensions.
+- `bucketed-rqmc`: one low-dimensional Sobol domain per `(trial, step, bucket)`.
+- `full-sort-array-rqmc`: a state-sorted oracle-style baseline using the same backend.
+- `step-rqmc-no-sort`: a negative baseline using the same backend without state matching.
+
+Use `--qmc-backend simple` to keep the dependency-free development backend, or `--qmc-backend openqmc-sobol` for the fair comparison.
